WEBVTT

00:01.801 --> 00:03.302
This is you?
- Yeah.

00:03.304 --> 00:04.636
Philanthropist.

00:04.638 --> 00:06.705
People pay for all sorts of
things on the Deep Web.

00:06.707 --> 00:08.874
I'm keeping custody of Jacob.

00:08.876 --> 00:11.210
But I lifted
the restraining order.

00:11.212 --> 00:14.546
Sometimes people keep trying
until they get it right.

00:14.548 --> 00:16.115
Why didn't you marry my dad?

00:16.117 --> 00:17.549
I don't want to talk about it.

00:17.551 --> 00:20.119
It's a simple question.
No, it's not!

00:21.187 --> 00:22.187
Jacob.

00:22.189 --> 00:23.322
Hi, Dad.

00:23.324 --> 00:24.323
Holy shit.

00:24.325 --> 00:26.525
Let go of him.
Please let go of him.

00:27.060 --> 00:30.696
She said to <i>please</i> let him go.

00:30.698 --> 00:31.897
Get out!
Get out of here!

00:31.899 --> 00:33.065
I<i> will</i> get my son.

00:33.067 --> 00:36.368
My attorney will be in touch.

00:36.370 --> 00:39.038
I need you to kill Sean.

00:42.342 --> 00:44.410
Why are you
- Looking at me like that?

00:44.412 --> 00:48.147
Because I am thinking about
what you just asked me to do.

00:48.149 --> 00:50.883
Are you thinking about
what you just asked me to do?

00:50.885 --> 00:52.918
No.
- I'm waiting for you to answer.

00:52.920 --> 00:55.220
I don't think
you meant to ask it.

00:55.222 --> 00:56.155
I did.

00:56.157 --> 00:58.057
You really
want me to kill Sean.

00:58.059 --> 00:59.425
I<i> need</i> you to kill Sean.

00:59.427 --> 01:00.659
Jacob's father.

01:00.661 --> 01:02.494
- Yes.
- You want to kill a person.

01:02.496 --> 01:05.831
No, I want<i> you</i> to kill a person,
which is nothing new for you.

01:05.833 --> 01:07.833
These are words I never imagined
you would say.

01:07.835 --> 01:09.902
And I never imagined
that the man who ruined me

01:09.904 --> 01:12.104
would come back
- And try to ruin me again.

01:12.106 --> 01:14.873
I never imagined
- He would try to ruin Jacob.

01:14.875 --> 01:17.576
Actually, I have imagined it
like a million times,

01:17.578 --> 01:19.678
because
- It's my worst nightmare.

01:19.680 --> 01:22.848
And now he wants custody
and he has a lawyer.

01:24.284 --> 01:25.851
I'm sorry.

01:25.853 --> 01:28.720
Of course,
I could never understand

01:28.722 --> 01:30.389
what you went through
with Sean.

01:30.391 --> 01:35.127
Obviously, it was horrible,
what he did to you.

01:35.129 --> 01:36.962
So you wouldn't have
kept Jacob a secret

01:36.964 --> 01:38.797
unless there was
a very good reason.

01:38.799 --> 01:40.099
Exactly.

01:40.101 --> 01:42.034
And that man cannot take Jacob.

01:42.036 --> 01:43.569
Do you understand?

01:43.571 --> 01:45.204
I understand.

01:45.206 --> 01:48.874
♪♪

01:52.145 --> 01:54.379
[ Sobs ]

01:56.116 --> 01:58.750
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

01:58.752 --> 02:01.553
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

02:01.555 --> 02:03.722
♪ Before you do something ♪

02:03.724 --> 02:06.125
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

02:06.127 --> 02:08.961
♪ Bricks are caving in ♪

02:08.963 --> 02:11.130
♪ Oh, how sweet this sin ♪

02:11.132 --> 02:13.966
♪ I left you the keys ♪

02:13.968 --> 02:16.135
♪ You won't let me in ♪

02:16.137 --> 02:18.737
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

02:18.739 --> 02:21.306
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

02:21.308 --> 02:23.775
♪ Before you do something ♪

02:23.777 --> 02:27.146
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

02:35.121 --> 02:37.022
[ Bell above door jingles ]

02:38.324 --> 02:40.526
Cul-de-sac?

02:40.528 --> 02:42.761
Sounds homey.

02:42.763 --> 02:45.764
Yeah, that sounds good, too.

02:45.766 --> 02:48.534
That's near the park, right?

02:48.536 --> 02:50.536
I like it.
I like it.

02:50.538 --> 02:52.771
Does the front yard
have privacy, though?

02:52.773 --> 02:56.208
Yeah, I don't want people
looking in on our shit.

02:56.210 --> 02:59.211
[ Laughs ]

02:59.213 --> 03:01.713
Okay, badass.

03:01.715 --> 03:04.383
Love you, too, baby.

03:04.385 --> 03:05.384
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:05.386 --> 03:07.553
My girl is researching
real estate,

03:07.555 --> 03:09.555
looking into school districts
and shit.

03:09.557 --> 03:12.124
You must be confident
you will get custody.

03:12.126 --> 03:14.459
- What can I get you?
- Just coffee.

03:16.229 --> 03:18.630
So your girlfriend
- Didn't want to come with you?

03:18.632 --> 03:19.865
Help support you?

03:19.867 --> 03:21.366
She knows
I fight my own battles.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.735
Obviously, Letty wants you
to fight this one.

03:23.737 --> 03:25.704
I am not here to fight.

03:25.706 --> 03:28.707
No? Then why'd you ask me
to meet you here?

03:28.709 --> 03:30.809
I know why.

03:30.811 --> 03:31.977
Really?

03:31.979 --> 03:33.912
You think I'm a piece of shit.

03:33.914 --> 03:35.314
I don't know you.

03:35.316 --> 03:37.683
So what happened
between you and Letty?

03:37.685 --> 03:39.418
She didn't tell you?

03:39.420 --> 03:41.086
No, not really.

03:41.088 --> 03:43.589
Letty and I had something...

03:43.591 --> 03:47.526
something real,
- Something real fucked-up.

03:47.528 --> 03:49.161
But she doesn't
take responsibility

03:49.163 --> 03:51.763
for the choices she makes,
and when shit turns bad,

03:51.765 --> 03:54.566
she turns blame on
whatever's close by.

03:54.568 --> 03:55.767
I was close by.

03:55.769 --> 03:57.202
Just an innocent bystander.

03:57.204 --> 03:59.605
No, I wasn't...
I wasn't perfect.

03:59.607 --> 04:03.075
But no matter what she wants to
believe, I wasn't a demon.

04:03.077 --> 04:04.776
Anyway, that was
a long time ago.

04:04.778 --> 04:06.845
I've moved on.

04:06.847 --> 04:08.780
I've become a man.

04:08.782 --> 04:11.283
A decade later,
and she is still

04:11.285 --> 04:14.119
right where she was
when I dropped her junkie ass.

04:14.121 --> 04:16.788
So you abandoned her.

04:16.790 --> 04:19.191
Junkies abandon themselves.

04:20.059 --> 04:21.393
You didn't do drugs.

04:21.395 --> 04:24.563
No, sure I did.
Nothing like Letty.

04:24.565 --> 04:29.568
I didn't even know that Jacob
existed until two weeks ago.

04:29.570 --> 04:32.271
She told him I was dead.
Did you know that?

04:32.273 --> 04:33.138
I know that.

04:33.140 --> 04:36.708
Well, I'm back from the dead.

04:43.883 --> 04:45.984
Thank you.

04:47.320 --> 04:48.920
So...

04:48.922 --> 04:52.791
how do you really know if you
want to be a father to Jacob?

04:52.793 --> 04:58.830
How do I know<i> if</i> I want to be
a father to my own son?

04:58.832 --> 05:02.067
You've only known Jacob for two
weeks, so you don't know him.

05:02.069 --> 05:04.002
I've spent more time with him
than you have.

05:04.004 --> 05:05.237
And that's the problem.

05:05.239 --> 05:06.438
Why is that a problem?

05:06.440 --> 05:07.939
You're not his real father.

05:07.941 --> 05:09.775
I care about
what happens to him.

05:09.777 --> 05:11.743
[ Chuckles ]

05:11.745 --> 05:14.813
You are unbelievable, man.

05:14.815 --> 05:17.182
You are disrupting
Jacob's life.

05:17.184 --> 05:18.417
He contacted me.

05:18.419 --> 05:20.252
A child doesn't always know
what's best.

05:20.254 --> 05:21.653
- I'm about to...
- What?

05:21.655 --> 05:23.422
What are you about to do?

05:25.425 --> 05:27.693
I think you should leave.

05:27.695 --> 05:29.294
That's a great idea.

05:29.296 --> 05:30.829
I mean leave.
Go away.

05:30.831 --> 05:33.865
I have never seen Letty more
destroyed than she is right now.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.834
You terrified her.

05:35.836 --> 05:37.536
Leave her alone.

05:37.538 --> 05:39.838
Leave Jacob alone.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.840
Are you kidding me with this?

05:41.842 --> 05:44.376
Jacob's an amazing kid

05:44.378 --> 05:47.279
because he was raised
by people who cared about him.

05:47.281 --> 05:49.548
And now you just want to take
him away from those people...

05:49.550 --> 05:51.149
his grandmother, his mother.

05:51.151 --> 05:53.385
Yeah. I want to take him
away from his mother,

05:53.387 --> 05:55.654
like she took him away from me.

05:55.656 --> 05:56.888
So you just want to win.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.490
Of course I want to win,

05:58.492 --> 06:01.960
but I choose my battles
carefully.

06:01.962 --> 06:04.229
Jacob is my son.

06:04.231 --> 06:05.964
That's a battle you choose.

06:05.966 --> 06:08.233
♪♪

06:12.805 --> 06:14.005
Can I help?

06:14.007 --> 06:16.341
We don't need help.

06:16.343 --> 06:21.079
I know you don't,
but I'm still gonna help.

06:31.057 --> 06:33.759
See?
I'm not so bad at this.

06:33.761 --> 06:34.926
It's an easy puzzle.

06:34.928 --> 06:37.095
They made it for drunk people.

06:44.170 --> 06:47.839
Swag I got from a cruise
Rob took me on.

06:49.575 --> 06:51.743
How long are you gonna
be mad at me?

06:51.745 --> 06:54.679
I don't know.

06:58.117 --> 07:00.118
[ Sighs ]

07:00.120 --> 07:02.954
Do you remember how many times I
asked you that same question...
[ Door slams ]

07:02.956 --> 07:04.689
you gave me that same answer?

07:04.691 --> 07:05.724
Yep.

07:05.726 --> 07:09.127
You two are so the same,
it's scary.

07:10.863 --> 07:13.432
Did you talk to Kyle yet?

07:13.434 --> 07:15.100
Not yet.

07:15.102 --> 07:18.570
You need a lawyer, Letty.

07:18.572 --> 07:20.872
Okay?

07:20.874 --> 07:23.809
Not just for you, for me.

07:23.811 --> 07:26.044
♪♪

07:26.046 --> 07:28.280
And I love that boy.

07:28.282 --> 07:32.918
I've cried for that boy,
I sacrificed for that boy,

07:32.920 --> 07:38.156
and I didn't do it all so that
repulsive piece of human garbage

07:38.158 --> 07:39.925
could come in here
- And take him away from us.

07:39.927 --> 07:42.294
I know you didn't.
- Well,
- that's what could happen.

07:42.296 --> 07:44.463
I won't let that happen.

07:44.465 --> 07:46.865
Good.

07:49.735 --> 07:51.269
Well, go.

07:51.271 --> 07:53.872
[ Children shouting
indistinctly ]

08:01.280 --> 08:03.248
[ Buzzer ]

08:05.518 --> 08:07.686
Ah. Jesus.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.187
Is the air-conditioning
broken?

08:09.189 --> 08:11.356
Oh, it sure is.

08:11.358 --> 08:15.293
It's like a damn heat wave.

08:15.295 --> 08:18.330
Don't tell me you think
you still work here.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.965
No.
I need to see Kyle.

08:19.967 --> 08:21.266
Is he here?

08:21.268 --> 08:24.536
He's here, but so is
Hurricane Tiffany.

08:24.538 --> 08:27.939
The filter is further up there,
Mitch.

08:27.941 --> 08:30.909
Put your back into it.

08:32.845 --> 08:35.313
Tiffany:
How could you think for a second
that people wouldn't find out?

08:35.315 --> 08:36.715
You're on Grindr
for Christ's sake.

08:36.717 --> 08:38.550
Would you keep it down?
I am not on Grindr.

08:38.552 --> 08:40.385
Really? So there's
some other dude who likes

08:40.387 --> 08:42.521
"getting deep-dicked till
he forgets his wife's name"

08:42.523 --> 08:44.956
standing five feet away from me
right now?

08:44.958 --> 08:47.359
Maybe it's Mitch.

08:47.361 --> 08:49.728
Sorry, I didn't
mean to interrupt.

08:49.730 --> 08:53.832
You did, but it's fine.
I got nothing left to say.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.166
What are you doing here?

08:55.168 --> 08:59.471
I need Kyle to make sure Sean
doesn't get custody of Jacob.

08:59.473 --> 09:01.306
Good luck with that.

09:01.308 --> 09:04.409
Yeah. [ Grunts ]

09:04.411 --> 09:07.679
Can you be my lawyer
for this custody hearing?

09:07.681 --> 09:09.814
It's tomorrow.
I'm sorry.

09:09.816 --> 09:10.916
Letty, you... you know

09:10.918 --> 09:12.751
that I don't know shit
about family law.

09:12.753 --> 09:14.219
So?
Open a book.

09:14.221 --> 09:17.389
Uh, my plate's
kind of full right now.

09:17.391 --> 09:19.090
You know this is everything.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.092
Can you please help me?

09:21.094 --> 09:23.361
Yes.
Okay, of course.

09:23.363 --> 09:24.930
Thank you.

09:27.199 --> 09:28.833
Oh, uh, hey.

09:28.835 --> 09:31.736
Wear something an unemployed
felon could actually afford.

09:31.738 --> 09:34.706
Yeah.

09:34.708 --> 09:37.809
♪♪

09:40.947 --> 09:42.747
I am sorry.

09:42.749 --> 09:44.282
Okay?

09:44.284 --> 09:46.918
Letty, I...

09:46.920 --> 09:49.454
I think that this whole thing
with Sean might have started

09:49.456 --> 09:51.022
because I accidentally
told Autumn

09:51.024 --> 09:54.392
that the actor on this
TV commercial was Jacob's dad,

09:54.394 --> 09:57.095
and I think that she told him,
and then he...

09:57.097 --> 09:59.030
That's exactly what happened.

09:59.032 --> 10:01.132
Why didn't you say anything?

10:01.134 --> 10:02.567
I don't know.

10:02.569 --> 10:05.203
It happened.
Can't change it.

10:05.205 --> 10:07.238
I know you have a lot going on.

10:07.240 --> 10:09.941
I am so sorry.

10:09.943 --> 10:11.643
It's okay.

10:11.645 --> 10:13.311
No, it's not.

10:13.313 --> 10:16.715
Well, hopefully, it will be.

10:19.752 --> 10:20.986
Want to go shopping?

10:20.988 --> 10:22.787
Yes.

10:22.789 --> 10:23.289
♪♪

10:27.494 --> 10:28.994
[ Both laugh ]

10:28.996 --> 10:31.830
Kyle said it has to look cheap,
not ugly.

10:31.832 --> 10:35.166
I can't believe he's already
dispensing fashion advice.

10:35.168 --> 10:36.801
Tiffany, he still loves you.

10:36.803 --> 10:38.837
He still wants to
sleep with you.

10:38.839 --> 10:41.172
Monogamy doesn't have to be
what it always was.

10:41.174 --> 10:42.907
Wrong.
Monogamy is a word.

10:42.909 --> 10:45.510
It has a definition.
- You know what I mean.

10:45.512 --> 10:48.279
You might find you'd like
an arrangement that's not so...

10:48.281 --> 10:50.649
traditional.

10:51.817 --> 10:54.352
Not bad.

10:54.354 --> 10:58.256
Remove the lace.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.458
You're seriously
gonna steal that?

11:00.460 --> 11:01.693
This is a charity store.

11:01.695 --> 11:04.362
- Ugh, fine.
- What is wrong with you?

11:04.364 --> 11:07.699
♪♪

11:11.203 --> 11:12.270
Hey, dude.

11:12.272 --> 11:14.606
Hey.
Is Jacob in his room?

11:14.608 --> 11:15.674
Sort of.

11:15.676 --> 11:18.443
He's in his fort,
which is in his room,

11:18.445 --> 11:20.712
and which is
the most badass fort, ever.

11:20.714 --> 11:23.114
I helped, but not that much.

11:23.116 --> 11:26.117
Estelle:
Did you talk to Kyle?

11:26.119 --> 11:28.353
Yeah, he'll be there.

11:28.355 --> 11:29.954
Thank God.

11:29.956 --> 11:31.523
Thank you.

11:39.065 --> 11:41.866
That is the best fort
I've ever seen.

11:41.868 --> 11:43.835
Can I come in?

11:43.837 --> 11:45.904
I'm reading.

11:45.906 --> 11:47.539
Just for a second.

12:03.089 --> 12:04.689
"Where the Red Fern Grows."

12:04.691 --> 12:06.524
I remember reading that book.

12:06.526 --> 12:08.560
This is my second time.

12:08.562 --> 12:10.395
Did it make you cry
the first time?

12:10.397 --> 12:12.330
No.

12:12.332 --> 12:14.999
Me neither.

12:15.835 --> 12:17.368
Know what the best part is?

12:17.370 --> 12:18.870
When the boy falls on the axe

12:18.872 --> 12:20.939
and a bubble of blood
comes out of his mouth.

12:20.941 --> 12:23.675
Totally.

12:26.078 --> 12:28.947
Are you nervous about
going to court tomorrow?

12:28.949 --> 12:31.049
I don't want to go.

12:31.051 --> 12:32.684
Me neither.

12:35.888 --> 12:37.889
I want everything
to go back to normal.

12:37.891 --> 12:39.624
I didn't think
you'd all start fighting

12:39.626 --> 12:41.392
just because
I e-mailed him.

12:41.394 --> 12:43.128
You didn't do anything wrong.

12:43.130 --> 12:45.563
Why do you want to
be my mom so bad?

12:45.565 --> 12:48.233
Because I<i> am</i> your mom.

12:48.235 --> 12:49.968
Because I love you.

12:49.970 --> 12:52.937
But aren't you supposed to not
lie to someone if you love them?

12:52.939 --> 12:55.306
You're right.
- I shouldn't have lied to you.

12:55.308 --> 12:57.408
I'll never do it again.

12:57.410 --> 13:00.445
I really want to be
a good mom to you.

13:00.447 --> 13:02.547
I know.

13:04.283 --> 13:05.817
I love you, too.

13:05.819 --> 13:09.487
♪♪

13:13.993 --> 13:15.393
Did you do it?

13:15.395 --> 13:16.394
No.

13:16.396 --> 13:18.029
Why?

13:19.899 --> 13:21.766
You know what?
Never mind.

13:21.768 --> 13:24.402
I'll get someone else to do it
off that Deep Web thing.

13:24.404 --> 13:25.670
I tried to get Sean to leave.

13:25.672 --> 13:27.338
That's not what
I asked you to do.

13:27.340 --> 13:28.807
Because Sean won't leave,

13:28.809 --> 13:30.809
which is why I didn't
ask you to ask him to leave.

13:30.811 --> 13:32.510
I asked you...
- What I don't want

13:32.512 --> 13:34.345
is to do the thing
you're asking me to do,

13:34.347 --> 13:35.647
and then you regret it.

13:35.649 --> 13:37.248
You will resent me
for doing something

13:37.250 --> 13:38.349
you don't really want done.

13:38.351 --> 13:39.951
He's going to
take him away from me.

13:39.953 --> 13:41.286
And me.

13:41.288 --> 13:42.854
I won't resent you.

13:42.856 --> 13:44.355
You will.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.558
I am not going to do it, Letty.

13:48.460 --> 13:50.695
Get out of this house.

13:52.998 --> 13:55.567
[ Door opens ]

14:03.209 --> 14:05.677
[ Dog barking in distance ]

14:06.312 --> 14:09.647
Woman: Room 213.
- Up the stairs, to the right.

14:09.649 --> 14:11.616
Thank you.
Have a good night.

14:18.991 --> 14:22.293
♪♪

14:24.997 --> 14:26.364
What are you doing here?

14:26.366 --> 14:29.200
I'm sleeping here.

14:31.237 --> 14:33.137
Please.

14:33.139 --> 14:36.441
♪♪

15:07.873 --> 15:09.240
Ow.

15:09.242 --> 15:10.775
Ah.

15:15.114 --> 15:16.614
[ Cries ]

15:16.616 --> 15:19.751
♪♪

15:31.230 --> 15:33.264
Cecile: Okay.

15:35.267 --> 15:37.235
Hi.
- Hi.

15:37.237 --> 15:39.737
- Are you...
- He's my mom's boyfriend.

15:39.739 --> 15:40.939
Hi, buddy.

15:43.809 --> 15:46.711
This is everyone now, correct?

15:46.713 --> 15:48.813
Yes.
We can get started.

15:48.815 --> 15:51.149
Actually, I'd like
to start with Jacob.

15:51.151 --> 15:52.450
Letty: Why? Sean: Why?

15:52.452 --> 15:54.752
Because
I'll speak with Jacob alone,

15:54.754 --> 15:56.955
and then I'll speak with
the rest of you.

15:56.957 --> 15:59.824
♪♪

15:59.826 --> 16:01.726
Is this normal?

16:12.471 --> 16:14.405
How are you doing?

16:15.007 --> 16:17.342
Is it normal that
they talk to the kid first?

16:17.344 --> 16:19.177
I-It's not
out of the question.

16:19.179 --> 16:20.611
But a kid could say anything.

16:20.613 --> 16:21.946
Jacob could say anything.

16:21.948 --> 16:23.748
Hey...

16:24.817 --> 16:27.185
Don't worry. Custody almost
always goes to the mother.

16:27.187 --> 16:28.519
Unless the mother is me

