36:44.836 --> 36:46.269
you will let us in.

36:51.542 --> 36:55.245
You really should've
led with that tidbit.

36:55.247 --> 36:57.814
I would've let you in
10 minutes ago.

36:57.816 --> 37:00.517
♪♪

37:00.519 --> 37:02.852
Who wants sandwiches?

37:02.854 --> 37:06.122
♪♪

37:10.928 --> 37:13.263
Lashever:
- No mayo on mine, thanks.

37:19.437 --> 37:21.104
None for me.

37:21.106 --> 37:23.740
- Calcium's good for the bones.
- Not mine.

37:23.742 --> 37:27.110
Well, it's your osteoporosis.

37:27.112 --> 37:28.945
If the lady
doesn't have to have milk,

37:28.947 --> 37:30.614
I shouldn't have to have milk.

37:30.616 --> 37:32.549
That makes sense.

37:32.551 --> 37:34.317
You still have to have milk.

37:40.758 --> 37:43.627
Come on, Jacob.
Let's go eat outside.

37:43.629 --> 37:45.562
Bye, Jacob.

37:45.564 --> 37:47.030
[ Door opens ]

37:49.300 --> 37:51.301
So, what, you turn yourself in?

37:51.303 --> 37:52.702
I got caught.

37:52.704 --> 37:54.804
Went in to quit,
they were waiting for me.

37:54.806 --> 37:56.706
Got fired, actually.

37:56.708 --> 37:58.275
Got fired.

37:58.277 --> 37:59.809
Thank you for clarifying.

37:59.811 --> 38:03.880
Your former parole officer,
here...

38:03.882 --> 38:06.316
Come here.

38:11.989 --> 38:15.392
So, your former parole officer,
here,

38:15.394 --> 38:18.295
starts telling us about
one of his former parolees,

38:18.297 --> 38:21.231
says she is the smartest
he ever worked with.

38:21.233 --> 38:24.134
Unconventional,
real sharp thinker,

38:24.136 --> 38:27.137
wears wigs, that she...

38:27.139 --> 38:30.240
and the she is you, Ms. Raines,
in case you weren't following...

38:30.242 --> 38:32.442
had something to do with
the $100,000

38:32.444 --> 38:36.179
he had rolled up in a duffel bag
full of cheap sweaters.

38:36.181 --> 38:39.182
You said something about
helping me get custody of Jacob?

38:39.184 --> 38:42.085
They will also expunge
your entire criminal record.

38:42.087 --> 38:43.853
- You'll be able to...
- Then he starts talking about

38:43.855 --> 38:48.124
this suave Latin guy that's
hanging around with this woman.

38:48.126 --> 38:51.261
Said he was real mysterious.

38:51.263 --> 38:52.862
Ding.

38:52.864 --> 38:55.365
I... I don't know.

38:55.367 --> 39:00.170
Something about the wigs
and the mysterious Latin guy...

39:00.172 --> 39:02.605
I just had a hunch
that he might be a guy

39:02.607 --> 39:06.976
we've been looking for
for a very long time...

39:06.978 --> 39:08.878
a guy named Javier.

39:08.880 --> 39:10.313
What did you mean when you said

39:10.315 --> 39:12.315
you can help me
get custody of my son?

39:12.317 --> 39:14.551
Finally, as you may have
guessed by now,

39:14.553 --> 39:17.287
your parole officer said
that you, Ms. Raines,

39:17.289 --> 39:19.155
under
- The right circumstances,

39:19.157 --> 39:22.392
might be willing to help me
locate this man.

39:22.394 --> 39:23.993
Well, he was wrong.

39:23.995 --> 39:25.528
That's interesting.

39:25.530 --> 39:28.631
I'm hoping that's not the case,
because, of course,

39:28.633 --> 39:32.635
if your current circumstances
do produce that willingness,

39:32.637 --> 39:36.539
it sure would minimize
the hailstorm of iced shit

39:36.541 --> 39:39.008
that's about to
- Come raining down on you.

39:39.010 --> 39:40.910
Just so you know,
the way you talk

39:40.912 --> 39:42.846
makes you sound like
an asshole.

39:42.848 --> 39:45.482
I'm an FBI agent,
Ms. Raines.

39:45.484 --> 39:48.351
I think you will find it easier
to deal with me

39:48.353 --> 39:49.986
if you change your attitude.

39:49.988 --> 39:52.422
Or you could change
your personality.
Letty.

39:52.424 --> 39:55.825
They will guarantee
you get custody of Jacob,

39:55.827 --> 39:58.261
and they'll wipe
your entire record.

39:58.263 --> 40:00.530
They can use it to
wipe their entire ass.

40:00.532 --> 40:04.100
You might be okay with selling
someone out, but I'm not.

40:04.102 --> 40:06.503
If I even knew who this guy was,
which I don't.

40:06.505 --> 40:07.771
Letty, I'm sorry.

40:07.773 --> 40:10.273
I'm sorry that I got caught,
but this is a good deal.

40:10.275 --> 40:14.444
I mean, they will erase
all of the shit from your past

40:14.446 --> 40:16.546
that stops you from...

40:16.548 --> 40:18.615
You can start over.

40:18.617 --> 40:20.049
Clean slate, with Jacob.

40:20.051 --> 40:23.186
Clean slate, with Jacob.

40:27.458 --> 40:28.458
For sure?

40:28.460 --> 40:30.293
For sure.

40:30.295 --> 40:31.961
Ms. Raines.

40:31.963 --> 40:35.465
We know your friend gets most of
his work through the Deep Web.

40:35.467 --> 40:39.135
All you have to do
is give us his handle,

40:39.137 --> 40:41.070
then we'll offer him a job.

40:41.072 --> 40:42.138
I can't do that.

40:42.140 --> 40:43.606
I think you can.

40:43.608 --> 40:44.707
I don't know him.

40:44.709 --> 40:46.543
[ Chuckles ] I think you do.

40:46.545 --> 40:47.977
I'm asking nicely,

40:47.979 --> 40:50.914
so I can see why you think you
have a little room to wiggle,

40:50.916 --> 40:53.650
but let me be clear with you.

40:53.652 --> 40:56.085
I can tell the judge
that he has no choice

40:56.087 --> 40:58.488
but to see the good in you
on Monday,

40:58.490 --> 41:00.156
that he has no choice on Monday

41:00.158 --> 41:02.592
but to see what a wonderful
mother you will be

41:02.594 --> 41:03.960
to little Jacob.

41:03.962 --> 41:06.129
Or I can do the opposite.

41:06.131 --> 41:07.831
Just do what she's asking.

41:07.833 --> 41:10.400
If he responds to our
job request, that's on him.

41:10.402 --> 41:13.236
We just need a little nudge
in the right direction.

41:13.238 --> 41:15.071
Nothing big, just a nudge.

41:15.073 --> 41:17.273
You want me to just nudge him
into a gas chamber.

41:17.275 --> 41:18.508
For the sake of little Jacob.

41:18.510 --> 41:20.443
Please stop calling him
little Jacob.

41:20.445 --> 41:23.179
You're making him sound like
a character from "Oliver Twist."

41:23.181 --> 41:24.514
I'm losing patience,
Ms. Raines.

41:24.516 --> 41:26.015
Please stop calling me
Ms. Raines.

41:26.017 --> 41:27.851
Please stop thinking
you have the power here.

41:27.853 --> 41:29.752
Oh, I definitely
have the power here.

41:29.754 --> 41:31.654
I don't know who that man is.

41:31.656 --> 41:33.756
You can leave now.

41:33.758 --> 41:35.525
If you change your mind,

41:35.527 --> 41:38.595
you have to do it
by the end of the day.

41:38.597 --> 41:39.796
♪♪

41:39.798 --> 41:41.464
Tomorrow is too late.

41:41.466 --> 41:43.800
Let me know.

41:43.802 --> 41:46.703
He has my info.

41:46.705 --> 41:47.205
♪♪

41:50.876 --> 41:53.042
[ Door opens, closes ]

41:53.044 --> 41:55.445
[ Groans ]

41:56.847 --> 41:58.214
I'm so sorry.

41:58.216 --> 41:59.549
How could you put me
in that position?

41:59.551 --> 42:01.217
Because I hunted you down
to a hotel

42:01.219 --> 42:04.153
where you convinced me
to help you steal $200,000

42:04.155 --> 42:06.055
and then I got arrested.
- You're saying this is my fault?

42:06.057 --> 42:08.358
- I'm saying you started it.
- Oh, my God.

42:08.360 --> 42:10.560
And I'm really glad you did.

42:10.562 --> 42:13.129
That was the best day
of my life.

42:13.131 --> 42:15.164
I'd do it all again.

42:15.166 --> 42:19.302
And if the final outcome of all
of this is you getting Jacob...

42:19.304 --> 42:21.070
I mean, holy shit.

42:21.072 --> 42:24.073
That'll be the best day
of<i> your</i> life.

42:27.878 --> 42:29.479
He's a murderer.

42:29.481 --> 42:31.381
Letty, all you have to do

42:31.383 --> 42:33.917
is give them his name
on that Web thing.

42:33.919 --> 42:36.152
You can even give it to me.
I'll give it to them.

42:36.154 --> 42:37.587
Javier is not a moron.

42:37.589 --> 42:39.856
If that car alarm of a woman
contacts him,

42:39.858 --> 42:41.190
he'll know something's up.

42:41.192 --> 42:43.426
Then there's nothing
to be conflicted about.

42:43.428 --> 42:47.664
Betrayal is not
- A tree falling in a forest.

42:47.666 --> 42:50.767
♪♪

42:59.577 --> 43:02.111
[ Clears throat ]

43:02.113 --> 43:05.448
You feel like telling me
why I was making sandwiches

43:05.450 --> 43:08.718
for your parole officer
and a fed this afternoon?

43:08.720 --> 43:11.654
Because
- You offered them sandwiches.

43:13.791 --> 43:15.758
I'll wait.

43:15.760 --> 43:17.226
[ Sighs ]

43:17.228 --> 43:19.862
They wanted me to rat
on one of my old dealers.

43:21.465 --> 43:22.699
Okay.

43:22.701 --> 43:25.635
And how does Jacob fit
into that request?

43:25.637 --> 43:29.639
In a quid pro quo sort of way.

43:29.641 --> 43:32.475
[ Sighs ]

43:32.477 --> 43:37.280
I-If you have a picture
of that drug dealer

43:37.282 --> 43:38.715
they want you to flip on,

43:38.717 --> 43:41.050
we could do
a side-by-side comparison,

43:41.052 --> 43:43.486
decide which one is cuter.

43:46.423 --> 43:50.093
Maybe I'm crossing the line
by asking,

43:50.095 --> 43:53.730
but where on earth
is that man of yours?

43:53.732 --> 43:55.665
He's not my man.

43:55.667 --> 43:58.434
Of course he is.

43:58.436 --> 44:03.239
If I were you,
I would go find him

44:03.241 --> 44:09.245
and apologize for
whatever it is you did.

44:09.247 --> 44:12.548
♪♪

44:55.125 --> 44:58.428
♪♪

45:06.637 --> 45:10.239
♪ It's gonna take
a bit of work ♪

45:11.809 --> 45:15.645
♪ Oh-ho, work ♪

45:17.514 --> 45:20.983
♪ Now that you're here ♪

45:23.087 --> 45:26.322
♪ Whoa-ho, work ♪

45:28.425 --> 45:31.594
♪ 'Cause people come and go ♪

45:33.831 --> 45:37.967
♪ But I think you should know ♪

45:41.105 --> 45:44.540
♪ That I ♪

45:44.542 --> 45:47.977
♪ I think this'll work ♪

45:50.781 --> 45:51.281
♪ Ooh ♪

45:58.189 --> 45:59.722
What can I get you?

45:59.724 --> 46:02.692
Oh, I think...

46:04.228 --> 46:05.461
I'll have a milkshake.

46:05.463 --> 46:08.631
Chocolate, vanilla,
or strawberry?

46:08.633 --> 46:09.799
I don't know.

46:09.801 --> 46:11.734
What do you think I should get?

46:11.736 --> 46:13.469
For you,
I'd go with strawberry.

46:13.471 --> 46:16.239
♪ It's gonna take
a little time ♪
Why's that?

46:16.241 --> 46:17.907
You want vanilla?

46:17.909 --> 46:21.878
No, I think you're right.
Strawberry.

46:24.148 --> 46:27.450
♪ I won't let go ♪

46:29.286 --> 46:32.889
♪ Till I got what's mine ♪

46:34.725 --> 46:38.294
♪ 'Cause people come and go ♪

46:40.497 --> 46:44.167
♪ But you should know ♪

46:44.169 --> 46:46.302
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

46:46.304 --> 46:48.004
♪ That I ♪

46:48.006 --> 46:53.843
♪ That I take it slow ♪

46:53.845 --> 46:54.944
Hi.

46:54.946 --> 46:56.412
Thanks for answering.

46:56.414 --> 46:56.914
♪ Ooh ♪

47:00.852 --> 47:01.918
Where are you?

47:01.920 --> 47:04.353
Nowhere, really.

47:05.956 --> 47:07.957
Nowhere?

47:07.959 --> 47:09.125
Where's that?

47:09.127 --> 47:12.028
I don't know.

47:12.030 --> 47:13.863
Are you sober?

47:13.865 --> 47:16.265
Are you my sponsor?

47:16.267 --> 47:18.334
I want to tell you something,

47:18.336 --> 47:20.036
and I want to do it
when you're sober.

47:20.038 --> 47:21.604
What is it?

47:21.606 --> 47:24.674
Tell me you're sober first.

47:24.676 --> 47:26.876
Jesus, yes. I'm sober.

47:26.878 --> 47:29.378
Just say what you have to say.

47:29.380 --> 47:33.516
I'm sorry I could not do
what you asked me to do.

47:33.518 --> 47:35.918
And I'm sorry I hurt you.

47:37.287 --> 47:38.487
Letty?

47:38.489 --> 47:41.023
♪ Oh-ho work ♪
- I'm here.

47:41.025 --> 47:42.959
Good.

47:42.961 --> 47:46.896
I wanted you to know that
before I say goodbye.

47:46.898 --> 47:48.464
What?

47:48.466 --> 47:51.033
You're not saying goodbye.

47:51.035 --> 47:53.736
I am.

47:53.738 --> 47:56.072
No, you're not.
- Don't be such a drama queen.

47:56.074 --> 47:58.007
Okay.

47:58.009 --> 47:59.208
It's still goodbye.

47:59.210 --> 48:02.078
- No, it's not.
- Take care of yourself, Letty.

48:06.516 --> 48:11.888
♪ Now that you're here ♪

48:11.890 --> 48:15.658
♪ Whoa-ho work ♪

48:33.010 --> 48:35.444
[ Chimes ]

